üîß What the Script Does
Installation Process:
Pre-check - Detects existing installations and offers reinstall/update options

Network Detection - Identifies network interface, gateway, and IP configuration

Base Packages - Installs essential dependencies (curl, git, golang, python, etc.)

Pi-hole Setup - Automated Pi-hole installation with custom upstream DNS

Unbound Configuration - Sets up recursive DNS resolver on port 5335

CoreDNS Deployment - Installs CoreDNS for additional DNS services

DoH Proxy - Configures DNS-over-HTTPS proxy for secure queries

Integration - Connects all components in a secure chain

DNS Flow:
text
Devices ‚Üí Pi-hole (Port 53) ‚Üí Unbound (Port 5335) ‚Üí Internet
                            ‚Üí CoreDNS (Port 8053)
                            ‚Üí DoH Proxy (Port 8054)
‚öôÔ∏è Services Installed
Service	Port	Purpose
Pi-hole	53	Primary DNS with ad-blocking
Unbound	5335	Recursive DNS resolver
CoreDNS	8053	Alternative DNS service
DoH Proxy	8054	DNS-over-HTTPS endpoint
üåê Post-Installation
Access the Pi-hole web interface at: http://YOUR_SERVER_IP/admin

Nginx Proxy Manager Configuration:
DoH (DNS-over-HTTPS):

Domain: dns.yourdomain.com

Forward to: YOUR_SERVER_IP:8054

Path: /dns-query

DoT (DNS-over-TLS):

Incoming port: 853

Forward to: YOUR_SERVER_IP:8053

üß™ Testing
After installation, the script performs automatic tests:

Unbound resolver functionality

Pi-hole DNS blocking

CoreDNS service

DoH proxy endpoint

üö® Important Notes
Static IP Required: Your server must have a static IP address

Manual Pi-hole Setup: During installation, choose "Custom" upstream DNS and enter 127.0.0.1#5335

Firewall: Ensure ports 53, 8053, 8054 are accessible as needed

Security: Change the default Pi-hole password after installation

